text: I saw Finding Dory tonight and had low expectations.  Actually, it was pretty good.  In this one, Dory is seeking her parents.  Marlin and Nemo come along to help,  there are shenanigans, she befriends an octopus, and the obligatory happy ending.  Side characters are both helpful and hilarious.  So yeah, it's a retelling of Finding Nemo, but it's well done and has a lot of funny moments, and nothing too adult for the children in attendance.  The four kids I brought loved it.  I smiled a lot and even laughed.  Ellen DeGeneres was really good in this.

text: I've seen "Finding Dory" and it was really good. I'm glad that studio wanted to make another sequel that the first one did it success last 12 years and I really love "Finding Nemo" which became Classic Disney/Pixar film. Now in the sequel, Dory must find her lost family that she doesn't remember where they are, but she found them in the located wildlife sea center at California and she tags along with Marylyn and Nemo and the rest of colorful fish buddies. Ellen finally coming back as memorable Dory and she did a good job for playing a fish memento character. I like her back story of her childhood which she tries to remember and she follows along with her path to find them. The movie does has some clever scenes like the colorful fish characters, Marylyn and Nemo were back again and they both did their roles good, and Dory's quest to parents is interesting. Even though, the scenes were same like the first one, but to be fair it's not so bad. Overall, a pretty good movie.
